# Incident Report – Case 04: Windows Process Anomaly Investigation

## Time of Activity
05/26/2026 (multiple timestamps)

---

## Summary
Multiple Sysmon alerts flagged unusual parent-child process relationships across Windows system processes. Investigation confirmed all were legitimate OS behavior.

---

## Affected Entities
- Hosts: win-3450, win-3451, win-3455
- Processes:
  - taskhostw.exe
  - rdpclip.exe
  - WUDFHost.exe
- Parents:
  - svchost.exe
  - services.exe

---

## Investigation Steps
- Checked process execution frequency
- Validated system file paths
- Correlated absence of malicious child processes
- Reviewed registry and persistence indicators

---

## Key Findings
- All binaries located in legitimate system directories
- No malicious child process execution
- No persistence or network anomalies
- Events match normal Windows service behavior

---

## Conclusion
False Positive – system process noise / detection rule tuning issue

---

## Escalation Decision
No escalation required

---

## Remediation Actions
- Tune detection rules for system processes
- Reduce noise from trusted Windows binaries
- Maintain baseline process whitelist

---

## Indicators of Interest
- rdpclip.exe
- taskhostw.exe
